Wooden tombs painted in various colours and limestone statues were among the treasures found in the 4 500-year-old burial ground. The oldest artefact discovered is a limestone family tomb from the fifth dynasty (around 2 5000 BC), said authorities. But perhaps the most prized object is a limestone statue of the tomb's owner, his wife, and son.   Mummified mice and more in latest Egyptian tomb discovery Dozens of mummified mice were among the animals found in a tomb dating back more than 2,000 years, unveiled by the Egyptian antiquities ministry with the aim of drawing tourists to the central Sohag province.